==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*arga-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[erch]] (Frisian [[erg]]), Middle Low German [[arch]] (Dutch [[erg]]), Old High German [[arg]] (German [[arg]] ‘bad’), Old Norse [[argr]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /æarx/

===Adjective===
'''earg'''
# [[cowardly]], [[timid]]
# [[evil]], [[bad]]

===Descendants===
*Scots [[ergh]], [[argh]]

